<h3>Why is this important?</h3>
<p>Sitting all day is bad for your health. Studies suggest that your risk of heart disease <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19996993" target="_blank">increases by nearly 64 percent</a>. Your average lifespan is reduced by <a href="http://sjp.sagepub.com/content/35/5/510.abstract" target="_blank">up to seven years</a>. And you have a higher risk for <a href="http://seer.cancer.gov/statfacts/html/colorect.html" target="_blank">certain types of cancer</a>. The good news is your Fitbit, and Fitminder, can help you counteract this desk chair disease.</p>

